[l] Infrastrukturapokalypse: Die Wasser-Grundversorgung in den USA steht wohl auf recht toenernen Fuessen.the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency projects it will cost $384 billion over 20 years just to maintain the nation's existing drinking water infrastructure. Replacing pipes, treatment plants and other infrastructure as well as expanding water systems to handle population growth could cost as much as $1 trillion.Wer Infrastruktur billig baut, baut zweimal.
